  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  with type 2 DM

          -  with uncontrolled glucose level on Metformin monotherapy over 1000mg /day (HbA1C over
             7%). Provided that the tolerance for metformin is poor, enrollment of patients with
             lower dose of metfomrin is open.

          -  who have never been prescribed with test drugs, sulfonylurea or DPP-4 inhibitor/GLP-1
             analogue in 3 months

          -  who can be applied with CGMS

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  who has liver function abnormality or renal function abnormality

          -  who has any kind of diseases, operations, medical treatments that can affect glucose
             levels
      </textblock>
